					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>184 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>255</height>
										<width>190</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>184 folios (+ 2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).  </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>One leaf is missing at the beginning and the first signature is at the end of folio 8. Folios 9-15 form the second quire, folios 16-23 the third, and folios 24-183 contain 16 quires of 10 leaves each. Folio 184 remains of the last quire, the rest having been cancelled. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Incomplete at the beginning.</p>
									<p>Two leaves are missing after folio 183. </p>
									<p>Several leaves at the beginning and at the end are mutilated. </p>
									<p>Marginal notes.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Uniform layout. Visible mastara ruling. </p>
									<p>Chapter numbers given in large characters. </p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
									<p>A few marginal notes. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
